content.text:
# QuickFixConnect Static Site

AI-Powered Tech & Marketing for Local Service Businesses

## Overview

This is a clean, modern static website for QuickFixConnect, built from scratch with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. The site showcases our AI marketing and tech services for local businesses.

## Features

- **Responsive Design** - Mobile-first approach with Tailwind CSS
- **AI Demo Video** - Embedded YouTube video showcasing our AI employee
- **Contact Forms** - GHL (GoHighLevel) form integration
- **Live Chat** - Tawk.to chat widget with mobile optimization
- **Real-time Metrics** - Animated dashboard cards with realistic data
- **Privacy Policy** - Complete privacy policy page
- **Brand Colors** - Custom color scheme (#00AEEF, #2BB673, #E8C19A)

## Tech Stack

- **HTML5** - Semantic markup
- **Tailwind CSS** - Utility-first CSS framework
- **JavaScript** - Vanilla JS for interactions and animations
- **Lucide Icons** - Modern icon library
- **Chart.js** - For sparkline charts

## Key Features

### Dashboard Cards
- **Realistic numbers** with counter animations (12 calls, 8 leads, 15 reviews)
- **Brand colors** throughout
- **Sparkline charts** for visual data representation

### AI Demo Video
- **Responsive iframe** with proper aspect ratio
- **Located in services section** for better context
- **Mobile optimized** display

### Contact Integration
- **GHL form** properly contained and sized
- **Tawk.to chat** with mobile optimization
- **Multiple contact methods** (phone, form, chat)

## Local development

This repo is a pure static site, so the simplest way to preview it locally is to run a tiny HTTP server.

```bash
cd QuickFiX2.0
./scripts/serve.sh
# then open: http://127.0.0.1:8080
```

Optional:

```bash
PORT=3000 ./scripts/serve.sh
HOST=0.0.0.0 ./scripts/serve.sh   # to test on another device on your LAN
```

## Deployment

This site is designed for deployment on:

- **Netlify** (recommended)
- **Vercel**
- **GitHub Pages**
- Any static hosting service

### Netlify Deployment

1. Connect your GitHub repository to Netlify
2. Netlify will auto-detect settings from `netlify.toml`
3. Deploy automatically!

### Environment Variables

No environment variables needed - this is a pure static site.

## File Structure

```
/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.html              # Homepage with all features
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ privacy.html            # Privacy policy page
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ assets/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ css/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ site.css        # Custom styles and animations
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ js/
‚îÇ   ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ app.js          # JavaScript functionality
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ img/                # Images
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ robots.txt              # SEO robots file
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sitemap.xml             # SEO sitemap
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ netlify.toml            # Netlify configuration
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ README.md               # This file
```

## Customization

### Colors
The site uses your brand colors:
- Primary: `#00AEEF` (Cerulean)
- Secondary: `#2BB673` (Sea Green)
- Accent: `#E8C19A` (Gold)

### Content Updates
- Edit HTML files directly for content changes
- Modify `assets/css/site.css` for styling changes
- Update `assets/js/app.js` for functionality changes

## Performance

- **Static site** - Lightning fast loading
- **Optimized assets** - Minified CSS and JS
- **CDN ready** - Perfect for global distribution
- **Mobile optimized** - Responsive design

## Contact

- **Email**: info@quickfixconnect.com
- **Phone**: 864-603-8052
- **Location**: Upstate, South Carolina

## License

¬© 2025 QuickFixConnect. All rights reserved.

# Run and deploy your AI Studio app This contains everything you need to run your app locally. View your app in AI Studio: https://ai.studio/apps/drive/1VCik8FnzDNvKwQUTNoXHvoASc1K8Xdlp ## Run Locally **Prerequisites:** Node.js 1. Install dependencies: `npm install` 2. Set the `GEMINI_API_KEY` in [.env.local](.env.local) to your Gemini API key 3. Run the app: `npm run dev`

# Galactic Alliance Terminal A high-fidelity communication interface simulating direct contact with the Galactic Alliance High Command. Built with React, TypeScript, Vite, and Google's Gemini AI API. View your app in AI Studio: https://ai.studio/apps/drive/1FRcxmwX0SALgdpnnczMuykT8T91dqO1Q ## Features - ü§ñ AI-powered chat interface with Google Gemini API - üé® Sci-fi themed terminal UI with Tailwind CSS - üíæ Local storage persistence for conversation history - üìä Real-time simulation metrics dashboard - üîí Secure API key management - ‚ö° Fast development with Vite - üì± Responsive design ## Prerequisites - **Node.js** 18+ (recommended: latest LTS version) - **npm** or **yarn** package manager - **Google Gemini API Key** - Get one from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey) ## Installation 1. **Clone the repository**: ```bash git clone cd Galactic-Terminal ``` 2. **Install dependencies**: ```bash npm install ``` 3. **Set up environment variables**: Create a `.env.local` file in the root directory: ```bash GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here ``` > **Note**: Copy `.env.example` to `.env.local` and fill in your API key, or create `.env.local` manually. 4. **Run the development server**: ```bash npm run dev ``` 5. **Open your browser**: Navigate to `http://localhost:3000` ## Available Scripts - `npm run dev` - Start development server - `npm run build` - Build for production - `npm run preview` - Preview production build locally ## Environment Variables ### Required - `GEMINI_API_KEY` - Your Google Gemini API key from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey) ### Setup 1. Get your API key from [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey) 2. Create `.env.local` in the project root 3. Add your API key: ``` GEMINI_API_KEY=your_actual_api_key_here ``` 4. Restart the development server > **Security**: Never commit `.env.local` to version control. It's already in `.gitignore`. ## Deployment See [DEPLOYMENT.md](./DEPLOYMENT.md) for detailed deployment instructions for: - Vercel - Netlify - GitHub Pages - Other platforms ### Quick Deploy to Vercel 1. Install Vercel CLI: `npm i -g vercel` 2. Run: `vercel` 3. Set `GEMINI_API_KEY` environment variable in Vercel dashboard ### Quick Deploy to Netlify 1. Install Netlify CLI: `npm i -g netlify-cli` 2. Run: `netlify deploy --prod` 3. Set `GEMINI_API_KEY` environment variable in Netlify dashboard ## Troubleshooting ### "GEMINI_API_KEY is not configured" Error **Problem**: The app shows an error about missing API key. **Solution**: 1. Ensure `.env.local` exists in the project root 2. Verify the file contains: `GEMINI_API_KEY=your_key_here` 3. Restart the development server 4. Check that the API key is valid and has proper permissions ### Build Errors **Problem**: `npm run build` fails. **Solution**: 1. Clear `node_modules` and reinstall: `rm -rf node_modules && npm install` 2. Clear Vite cache: `rm -rf node_modules/.vite` 3. Ensure all dependencies are installed: `npm install` 4. Check Node.js version: `node --version` (should be 18+) ### API Connection Errors **Problem**: Messages fail to send or show connection errors. **Solution**: 1. Verify your API key is correct and active 2. Check your internet connection 3. Ensure you haven't exceeded API rate limits 4. Check browser console for detailed error messages ### Styles Not Loading **Problem**: UI looks broken or styles are missing. **Solution**: 1. Ensure Tailwind CSS dependencies are installed: `npm install` 2. Rebuild: `npm run build` 3. Clear browser cache 4. Check that `index.css` is being imported in `index.tsx` ## Project Structure ``` Galactic-Terminal/ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/ # React components ‚îÇ ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Dashboard.tsx # Metrics dashboard ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Terminal.tsx # Chat terminal interface ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ services/ # API services ‚îÇ ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ geminiService.ts # Gemini API integration ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ App.tsx # Main application component ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.tsx # Application entry point ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.html # HTML template ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ index.css # Global styles with Tailwind ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ types.ts # TypeScript type definitions ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ vite.config.ts # Vite configuration ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tailwind.config.js # Tailwind CSS configuration ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ postcss.config.js # PostCSS configuration ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ package.json # Dependencies and scripts ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ tsconfig.json # TypeScript configuration ``` ## Technologies Used - **React 19.2.3** - UI framework - **TypeScript** - Type safety - **Vite 6.2.0** - Build tool and dev server - **Tailwind CSS 3.4** - Utility-first CSS framework - **Google Gemini API** - AI chat backend - **localStorage** - Client-side persistence ## License This project is private and proprietary. ## Support For issues and questions: 1. Check the [Troubleshooting](#troubleshooting) section 2. Review error messages in browser console 3. Check deployment logs if deployed --- **Built with ‚ù§Ô∏è for the Galactic Alliance**

# Aurelian language workspace

This folder contains evolving specs and drafts generated with Cardona.

## Files
- `SYSTEM-BRIEF-v1-FOR-AGENTS.md` ‚Äî execution-only constitution for agents (canonical constraints)
- `SYSTEM-PROMPT-v1-FOR-AGENTS.txt` ‚Äî tight copy/paste system prompt + conformance block
- `OPERATORS-v1.md` ‚Äî operators & structure (draft)
- `CORPUS-v1.md` ‚Äî starter corpus (draft)
- `SCHEMA-v1.md` ‚Äî lossless mapping draft
- `BOOK1-PHILOSOPHY-v1-DRAFT.md` ‚Äî bilingual philosophy ‚ÄúBook I‚Äù draft + proposed operators/roots
- `BOOK1-PHILOSOPHY-v1.1.md` ‚Äî refined working draft

## Notes
- v1 structural decision: grammar/structure is lexical (particles/word order/connectors), not punctuation.
- Punctuation may appear stylistically but must not carry grammatical meaning.
